Welcome to the demographic information input form for the .

This form contains XX questions. 
You will be asked about your:

  • Country of Origin, Language and Culture
  • Location
  • Sex and Gender
  • Occupation and Education
  • Health and Disability

The information you provide here will not be attached to your name, contact details or other specific identifying information about you. We call this "deidentified" data. 

If you have any questions or concerns about participating please see the Participant Information Sheet (LINK NEEDED). 

 

Why do you need this information about me for this research?

These questions are very important for our research, as we are hoping to ensure we can collect data from a wide range of people with a variety of experiences.

That way, when we write up conclusions about the research we can be accurate in saying which groups in our communities the data describes well, and which groups might need more attention in the future to be represented. 

We are also hoping to create tools for clinical neuropsychologists to use when they see people from a range of different backgrounds. For example, some activities used for checking cognitive health are easier for people who have spoken English their whole life, and harder for people who learn English later in life. Ideally, we could use activities in people's first languages, however, often that isn't an available option. 

If someone struggles with an activity, clinical neuropsychologists want to be sure about why that might be, and avoid mistakes due to language or other social differences!

So, your demographic information can help us to identify if there are ways to make it more 'fair' when doing a check up on people's cognitive health.
